**Standing instructions (source of truth):** All four Claude Cowork tasks read a single Google Drive file at startup. This file contains persistent formatting preferences, rules, and structural notes that override the task's default prompt. Any approved change from the feedback loop is applied here first, then picked up automatically by all tasks on the next run.

- Google Drive file ID: `1nhgIPfLN1xj52r6cx8RLZ4AD1klzJYt5uB-QPl_-UiU`

**Slack auth guard:** All four Claude tasks begin with a 1-message read of #b2b-cos as a connectivity test. If Slack authentication is broken, the task creates a Gmail draft to `danny.jozsef@nubank.com.br` with subject `[ALERT] <Task Name> — Slack reconnection needed` and exits immediately without posting.

