### What counts as a "notable item"

- A decision made or announced
- A milestone reached or go-live confirmed
- A risk or blocker raised that leadership should know about
- A cross-area coordination topic
- A concrete commercial development (deal progress, partnership update, merchant activation)

Does NOT count: casual conversation, FYIs with no action implication, items already covered in that week's Top of Mind, routine operational updates.

### Output format

```
`B2B Digest` — {Day DD Mon}, 19h

*HIGHLIGHTS* :dart:
• [Notable item] — <#CHANNEL_ID> (date, time)
• [Notable item] — <#CHANNEL_ID> (date, time)
...

*OPERATIONAL RADAR* :construction:
• [Item] — <#CHANNEL_ID>    ← omit entire section if nothing qualifies

*Sent using @Claude*
```

Immediately after posting, Claude posts a thread reply with sources:

```
`Sources`
• [Author] — <#CHANNEL_ID> ([date, time])
...
```

**Rules:** Max 6 items in Highlights, 3 in Operational Radar. The `*Sent using @Claude*` line appears exactly once at the very end. Channel references use `<#CHANNEL_ID>` format (Slack renders as clickable link), never plain text names. All numbers use Brazilian notation.

### João Banzato's channel (C0B19T1K4BA)

Any new posts from João are included as a brief one-liner on what João is looking at or investigating. This channel has dedicated coverage at Mixed priority.

