## 5. B2B Feedback Review

**Type:** Claude Cowork scheduled task  
**Cadence:** Every Friday, ~17:00 BRT  
**Posts to:** Private DM to Danny only (never to #b2b-cos)  
**Sender:** Claude (via Slack MCP, DM to Danny's user ID `U01JEEX0XHU`)

### What it does

Every Friday the task reads the last 50 messages in #b2b-cos, finds the most recent post of each report type (Merchant Monitor, Top of Mind, Daily Digest, M-Team Update), reads any thread replies on those posts, and classifies each reply as:

- **STRUCTURAL** — a recurring theme, explicit format change, data field to always add/remove, or standing rule that should apply to every future run.
- **ONE-OFF** — a correction to a specific post, comment about a specific week, praise without actionable change.

Only STRUCTURAL items are surfaced. Items already present in the standing instructions Google Drive file are filtered out.

### Output (when proposals found)

```
:brain: *B2B CoS — Weekly Feedback Review*
_Here is what I found in #b2b-cos threads this week that seems worth making permanent in the standing instructions:_

*[Report type]*
1. [Feedback item] — from @name ([date])
   → Suggested addition: "[exact text to add to standing instructions]"

*[Report type]*
2. ...

_To apply these, open Cowork and say "approve items 1, 3" (or "approve all"). I'll update the standing instructions in Google Drive automatically — no manual editing needed._
```

### Output (when nothing new found)

```
:brain: *B2B CoS — Weekly Feedback Review*
Nothing new to add to the standing instructions this week. All thread feedback was either one-off or already covered.
```

### Approval flow

Danny receives the DM, opens a Cowork session, and says "approve items X" or "approve all". Claude then updates the Google Drive standing instructions file and, if needed, updates the relevant task prompts. No manual editing of the Drive file or task configs is required.

A local convenience copy of pending proposals is written to `feedback-pending.md` during each Friday run. It is overwritten every week (no accumulation of old proposals).

